Subinterfaces of QueryEngine in com.googlecode.cqengine
 interface IndexedCollection<O>
          A Java collection which can maintain indexes on the objects it contains, allowing objects matching complex queries to be retrieved with very low latency.
 

Classes in com.googlecode.cqengine that implement QueryEngine
 class ConcurrentIndexedCollection<O>
          An implementation of Set and QueryEngine, thus providing ConcurrentIndexedCollection.retrieve(com.googlecode.cqengine.query.Query) methods for performing queries on the collection to retrieve matching objects, and ConcurrentIndexedCollection.addIndex(com.googlecode.cqengine.index.Index) methods allowing indexes to be added to the collection to improve query performance.
 class ObjectLockingIndexedCollection<O>
          Extends ConcurrentIndexedCollection with some specialized locking for applications in which multiple threads might try to add or remove the same object to/from an indexed collection concurrently.
 class TransactionalIndexedCollection<O>
          Extends ConcurrentIndexedCollection with support for READ_COMMITTED transaction isolation using Multiversion concurrency control (MVCC).
